{# Revenue Model - the JSON object represents a set of revenue-related configurations.

To build Revenue Model you have to:
1. Define the Category Name. The category name is the key in the JSON object (e.g., "large_group_reservation"). Name of the category also must be included in the _utilsGetConversationCategoriesSkill for your industry

2. Structure the Category.
Each category is a dictionary/object with the following components:
	•	revenue_parameters_schema: Defines the input data structure (schema) required for to calculate potential revenue. Is used to get those parameters from the conversation.
	•	potential_revenue_formula: Provides the formula to calculate the potential revenue.
	•	constants: Holds fixed values or constants used in the formula.
	•	min_value: Is set if final sum is less then this value.
	•	zero_default: Is set if final sum is equal to zero.

In some cases you can provide only fixed_potential_revenue. It means that value from that field will be returned as is without any calculations.

Example:
{
  "order": {
    "fixed_potential_revenue": "70"
  },
  "booking": {
    "revenue_parameters_schema": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "party_size": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Number of people for reservation"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "party_size"
      ]
    },
    "potential_revenue_formula": "party_size * average_bill_per_person",
    "constants": {
      "average_bill_per_person": "50",
      "call_center_savings": "0"
    },
    "min_value": 200, (optional) in case the final sum is less then this value, this will be applied instead
    "zero_default" 200, (optional) in case if the final sum is 0, this will be applied instead
  }
} #}

